[u][b]Installation Instructions[/b][/u]:
[spoiler="Expand to see installation instructions for this tool"]
[list type=decimal]
[li]Download [url="https://www.gimp.org/downloads/"]GIMP[/url] (version 2.10.10 or later required).[/li]
[li]Install [url="http://gimpchat.com/viewtopic.php?f=9&t=20613&start=80#p285476"]gegl-python-fu & gegl_graph Ver.3.0.zip by MareroQ[/url] and install it to your GIMP plugins directory (default location is [b][font=Courier New][color=#ba8bff]C:\Users\(Your Username)\AppData\Roaming\GIMP\2.10\plug-ins[/color][/font][/b]).[/li]
[li]Install download [url="https://pngquant.org"]pngquant[/url] (the "Binary for Windows" version) and install it to [b][font=Courier New][color=#ba8bff]C:\Windows[/color][/font][/b][/li]
[li]Download the Marvel Mods GIMP Scripts.[/li]
[li]Open [b][font=Courier New][color=#ba8bff]update.bat[/color][/font][/b] with Notepad++ or another text editor.[/li]
[li]Edit the file paths in line 6 and line 8 to reflect your GIMP configuration.[/li]
[li]Save [b][font=Courier New][color=#ba8bff]update.bat[/color][/font][/b][/li]
[li]Run [b][font=Courier New][color=#ba8bff]update.bat[/color][/font][/b] as an administrator, which will allow you to access the necessary folders.[/li]
[/list]
[/spoiler]


